# Pre-Researcher — solo-law

Answering Q1–Q6 from plan-gate.out.

---

## Q1 — Accent color (definitive)

**Use `#C9A96E` (antique gold) as the primary accent.**

Rationale: Elite law firm sites universally use one muted metallic accent against
B&W. Pure gold (#D4AF37, #FFD700) reads cheap at screen resolution. #C9A96E is
warm, editorial, and subdued — fits the "expensive but not loud" brief exactly.
Use it at full opacity only for CTAs and ruled lines; 40% opacity for decorative
dividers.

Full palette:
- Background: `#0D0D0D` (near-black, not pure black — avoids harsh contrast)
- Surface: `#141414`
- Text primary: `#F5F3EF` (warm white)
- Text secondary: `#9E9E9E`
- Accent: `#C9A96E` (antique gold)
- Accent hover: `#B8955A`
- Danger/error: `#C0392B`

