## Q4 — Playwright WebGPU headless flags

**Production test launch args (Linux CI with hardware GPU):**
```js
launchOptions: {
  args: [
    '--headless=new',
    '--use-angle=vulkan',
    '--enable-features=Vulkan,WebGPU',
    '--disable-vulkan-surface',
    '--enable-unsafe-webgpu',
    '--ignore-gpu-blocklist',
  ]
}
```

**CI without GPU (most cloud runners — GitHub Actions, etc.):**
WebGPU will be unavailable (`navigator.gpu === undefined`). This is the key
trigger for the mock-fallback path. Design `AiAgentService` to check:
```ts
const gpuAvailable = typeof navigator !== 'undefined' && !!navigator.gpu;
```
If false, skip WebLLM load entirely and use a hardcoded mock reflection/evaluation
response. Playwright in CI without GPU args will hit this path automatically —
write tests to assert mock-fallback UI renders correctly rather than testing the
full WebGPU inference path (which requires real GPU hardware).

**For local dev / staging testing with GPU:** add the Vulkan flags above in
`playwright.config.ts` under `projects[x].use.launchOptions`.

